Description: Fragment of a clay figurine made of a brown fine Nile clay. The preserved piece is broken into three joining fragments that form an elongated cylindrical shape that ends in a smaller flattened part like a foot of a figurine.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D15.N (sand), Mound β
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 212)
